description:
python<->objc interoperability module

pyobjc is a bridge between python and objective-c.  it allows full
featured cocoa applications to be written in pure python.  it is also
easy to use other frameworks containing objective-c class libraries
from python and to mix in objective-c, c and c++ source.

this package is a pseudo-package that will install all pyobjc related
packages (that is, pyobjc-core as well as wrappers for frameworks on
macos)

documentation_summary: The HTML text is about the GitHub repository "ronaldoussoren/pyobjc," which is a project that serves as a bridge between Python and Objective-C, providing bindings for macOS frameworks. It includes a variety of Python packages for easy installation and usage, specifically targeting Python versions 3.6, 3.7, and 3.8, with regular testing on the development version of Python. However, it does not support PyPy, Jython, and IronPython. The repository is intended for feature development and is considered unstable; users are advised to use the latest release instead. The repository has 491 stars, 41 forks, and is watched by 14 people.
